After clearing the JWT and reloading, the mobile context occasionally
captured the React 'Loading...' splash before fetchAuthStatus had
returned, then flagged a false-positive 'auth state stuck' warning.
Wait for the splash text to disappear (or 8s timeout) before deciding
whether the login form rendered, so the assertion only fires when the
app has actually settled into a state.
